---
import Prose from './primitives/Prose.astro';
import Stack from './layout/Stack.astro';

// "How a working session feels" — NOW card, owner split (you vs Hermes), and feedback update
---

<hr class="section-rule" aria-hidden="true" />

<section aria-labelledby="session-title">
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">03 /</span>
    <h2 id="session-title" class="section-title">How a working session feels</h2>
  </div>

  <Prose class="intro" measure={false}>
    Every session starts with one card: the current primary next action. No open loops, no context switching.
    Every item has an owner — either you or your AI agent — and ownership is explicit.
  </Prose>

  <Stack gap={5}>
    <div class="now-card" role="figure" aria-label="Session view example">
      <div class="now-index">
        NOW<br />
        <span>01</span>
      </div>
      <div class="now-copy">
        <div class="label">Primary next action</div>
        <div class="now-action-text">
          Draft Q3 OKRs for the product team
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ownership">
        <span class="label">Owned by</span>
        <strong>You</strong>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="now-card" role="figure" aria-label="AI agent session view">
      <div class="now-index">
        NOW<br />
        <span>02</span>
      </div>
      <div class="now-copy">
        <div class="label">Primary next action</div>
        <div class="now-action-text">
          Run test suite &amp; report failures
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ownership">
        <span class="label">Owned by</span>
        <strong>Hermes (AI agent)</strong>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Stack>

  <p style="font: 12px / 1.5 var(--mono); color: var(--muted); margin-top: 20px;">
    ↔ When a card is done, the owner signals completion. Analysis runs, feedback loops fire,
    and the next primary action surfaces. No orphaned projects.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .intro {
    max-inline-size: var(--measure-legacy-wide);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-6);
  }
</style>

